HEADWORD: Cœnogamy
<hw>C⟦oe⟧*nog"a*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>koino`s</grk> common + <?/ marraige.]</ety> <def>The state of a
community which permits promiscuous sexual intercourse among its
members; -- as in certain primitive tribes or communistic
societies.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>cenogamy</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

